Main Games.d:
Survive in a post-apocalyptic world following a catastrophic nuclear power plant disaster. Scavenge for superior equipment and conquer the wastelands to become their ruler. Decide whether to work with your faction or betray it. The fate of your legacy is in your hands.

This game is a true test of your survival and PvP skills. Prepare to face challenges that will test your abilities to the fullest.

Experience the ultimate gaming immersion with state-of-the-art Roblox graphics, featuring full PBR materials.

Please be aware that this game is still in development and does not represent the final product. Expect frequent updates and occasional restarts. While your skins and delta currency will be retained, player inventories and non-permanent items may be reset with significant updates.

Special Credits:
We are inspired by the original Deadzone on Roblox and express our sincere appreciation to its creator for the incredible game idea that ignited our own creative journey.

>> THIS GAME IS IN EARLY ACCESS <<
Please note that, as with any early access, there might be a few hiccups in your experience, but your feedback is vital in shaping the game.
It is highly recommended that you play the tutorial before buying early access!

Blackout is a dynamic looter shooter where factions dominate, and your choices determine your fate. Scavenge, adapt, and engage with tasks in an evolving landscape.
Surviving alone is very difficult, and making allies along your journey is crucial.

ANIME X SHOWDOWN

Premium:
- Double base rewards in AFK World

Commands:
!redeem [code]
!join [friend]

Controls:
  - Shift (Hold): Sprint
  - M1: Basic Attack
  - M2: Heavy Attack
  - Space (Hold) + M1 (On Ground): Uptilt
  - Space (Hold) + M1 (In Air): Air Launcher
  - M2 (In Air): Aerial Slam
  - Q: Dash
  - F: Block
  - F (Timed, on specific moves): Perfect Block
  - C: Move Meter Charge
  - R: (when bottom white gauge is full): Evasive
  - X: (When orange icon above moves is visible): Assault Dash

Moves:
  - Not all skills are perfect blockable.
  - Moves cost Move Meter (Blue meter at the top), which you can get back from charging with the C key or landing M1 attacks.

Armor Levels:
  - Super Armor is weaker than Hyper Armor.
  - Super Armor absorbs 50% damage rather than all 100% on non armor-breaking moves.
  - Some skills can BREAK Armor, this means they can cancel an attack with Armor.
  - Hyper Armor Break can cancel Super Armor and Hyper Armor moves.
